targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  "timestamp",
  prediction,
  id
FROM
  api_inferences
ORDER BY
  "timestamp" DESC
LIMIT
  50;
SELECT request_data, prediction FROM api_inferences LIMIT 50

SELECT prediction, (request_data->>'ApplicantIncome')::numeric AS applicant_income
FROM api_inferences;

panels.title: Applicant Income Distribution by Prediction Outcome

targets.rawSql:
SELECT 
    CASE 
        WHEN (request_data->>'Credit_History')::numeric = 1 THEN 'with credit history' 
        WHEN (request_data->>'Credit_History')::numeric = 0 THEN 'without credit history' 
        ELSE 'unknown'
    END AS credit_history,
    prediction, 
    COUNT(*) AS total
FROM api_inferences
GROUP BY credit_history, prediction;

SELECT 
    CASE 
        WHEN prediction = '1' THEN 'accepted' 
        WHEN prediction = '0' THEN 'denied' 
        ELSE 'unknown'
    END AS prediction_status,
    avg_loan_amount
FROM (
    SELECT 
        prediction, 
        AVG((request_data->>'LoanAmount')::numeric) AS avg_loan_amount
    FROM api_inferences
    GROUP BY prediction
) AS subquery;

SELECT CASE
         WHEN DATE(timestamp) < '2024-01-01' THEN 'Before 2024'
         ELSE 'After 2024'
       END AS period,
       AVG((request_data->>'LoanAmount')::numeric) AS avg_loan_amount
FROM api_inferences
GROUP BY period;

panels.title: Comparison of Average Loan Amount Before and After a Specific Date

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  request_data->>'Education' AS education,
  AVG((request_data->>'LoanAmount')::numeric / NULLIF((request_data->>'ApplicantIncome')::numeric + (request_data->>'CoapplicantIncome')::numeric, 0)) AS avg_loan_to_income_ratio
FROM api_inferences
GROUP BY education;

panels.title: Average Loan Amount to Income Ratio by Education Level

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  WIDTH_BUCKET((request_data->>'LoanAmount')::numeric, 0, 10000, 10) AS loan_amount_bucket,
  WIDTH_BUCKET((request_data->>'ApplicantIncome')::numeric, 0, 50000, 10) AS income_bucket,
  request_data->>'Married' AS married_status,
  COUNT(*) AS application_count
FROM api_inferences
GROUP BY loan_amount_bucket, income_bucket, married_status
ORDER BY loan_amount_bucket, income_bucket, married_status;

panels.title: Loan Amount and Applicant Income by Marital Status

targets.rawSql:
WITH hourly_averages AS (
  SELECT DATE_TRUNC('hour', timestamp) AS hour,
         AVG((request_data->>'LoanAmount')::numeric) AS avg_loan_amount
  FROM api_inferences
  GROUP BY hour
)
SELECT hour,
       avg_loan_amount,
       (avg_loan_amount - LAG(avg_loan_amount) OVER (ORDER BY hour)) / NULLIF(LAG(avg_loan_amount) OVER (ORDER BY hour), 0) * 100 AS hour_over_hour_change
FROM hourly_averages
ORDER BY hour;

panels.title: Hourly Change in Average Loan Amount

targets.rawSql:
SELECT DATE(timestamp) AS date,
       (request_data->>'LoanAmount')::numeric AS loan_amount,
       RANK() OVER (PARTITION BY DATE(timestamp) ORDER BY (request_data->>'LoanAmount')::numeric DESC) AS rank
FROM api_inferences
ORDER BY date, loan_amount DESC;

panels.title: Rank Applications by Loan Amount within Each Day

targets.rawSql:
WITH daily_totals AS (
  SELECT DATE(timestamp) AS date,
         COUNT(*) AS total
  FROM api_inferences
  GROUP BY date
)
SELECT date,
       total,
       SUM(total) OVER (ORDER BY date) AS running_total
FROM daily_totals
ORDER BY date;

SELECT DATE(timestamp) AS date,
       request_data->>'Education' AS education,
       prediction,
       COUNT(*) AS total
FROM api_inferences
GROUP BY date, education, prediction
ORDER BY date, education;

SELECT DATE(timestamp) AS date,
       COUNT(DISTINCT prediction) AS distinct_predictions
FROM api_inferences
GROUP BY date
ORDER BY date;

SELECT DATE(timestamp) AS date, prediction, COUNT(*) AS total
FROM api_inferences
GROUP BY date, prediction
ORDER BY date;

SELECT DATE(timestamp) AS date,
       AVG((request_data->>'LoanAmount')::numeric) AS avg_loan_amount,
       AVG((request_data->>'ApplicantIncome')::numeric) AS avg_applicant_income
FROM api_inferences
GROUP BY date
ORDER BY date;
